<TITLE> Memorial anthology out on Shamsur Rahman's birthday </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Oct 23 (bdnews24.com)A memorial anthology of 72 select writings was published on Friday marking the 80th birth anniversary of eminent Bengali poet Shamsur Rahman. National professor Kabir Chowdhury launched the memorial anthology in the morning at his residence in Ghazi Bhaban in Paltan in the capital. "Many books have been written about the poet Shamsur Rahman and his poetry and many more will be written in the future," said professor Chowdhury. "Rahman was honoured and acclaimed as a great Bangla poet at home and abroad. He captured the natural bounties, heroism, struggle, glory, sacrifice and love of Bangladesh, of the Bangladeshis in his poems. "His works have been translated in other languages and widely read by the people at large. The poet will live as long as Bangla as a language should live." The Tk 300 anthology has been enriched by contributions from Syed Shamsul Haq, Sunil Gangopadhyay, William Radice, Serajul Islam Chowdhury, Abdul Gaffar Chowdhury, Muntasir Mamun and other eminent writers. Shamsur Rahman was born on Oct 23, 1929 in Mahuttuli in the city and breathed his last on Aug 17, 2006. Working as a journalist for many years, Rahman wrote profusely throughout his life turning out illustrious volumes of short stories, novels as well as translated works. b
